# Assets and Icons Rule

All icon and image assets must be imported in the constants layer and used from there. No component or file may import directly from `src/assets/`.

## Icons

- **File:** `src/constants/icons.constants.ts`
- **Scope:** Any asset used as an icon (e.g. all `*-icon.png` files in `assets/`).
- **Rule:** Import every icon from `src/assets/` (or `src/assets/icons/` if you use a subfolder) into `icons.constants.ts` and export it on the `ICONS` object. Use a clear UPPER_SNAKE_CASE name (e.g. `CROSS_ICON`).
- **Usage:** In components, import from `constants/icons.constants` and use the exported value (e.g. `ICONS.CROSS_ICON`). Do not import from `assets/` or `assets/icons/` in components.

## Images

- **File:** `src/constants/images.constants.ts`
- **Scope:** All other images (e.g. photos, illustrations, logos that are not icon-only) in `src/assets/`.
- **Rule:** Import every such image from `src/assets/` into `images.constants.ts` and export it on the `IMAGES` object. Use a clear UPPER_SNAKE_CASE name.
- **Usage:** In components, import from `constants/images.constants` and use the exported value (e.g. `IMAGES.HERO`). Do not import from `assets/` in components.

## Summary

| Asset type | Constants file           | Export object | Example usage in code        |
|-----------|--------------------------|---------------|------------------------------|
| Icons     | `icons.constants.ts`     | `ICONS`       | `import { ICONS } from '...'; <img src={ICONS.CROSS_ICON} />` |
| Images    | `images.constants.ts`    | `IMAGES`      | `import { IMAGES } from '...'; <img src={IMAGES.HERO} />`     |

When adding a new icon or image: add it to the correct constants file first, then use the exported constant everywhere. Never use a path like `@/assets/...` or `../assets/...` in components.
